.row
  .col-xs-12
    %p
      Apart from configuring your bot, you will need to do some configuration steps at Slack side.
.row
  .col-xs-12
    #instructions.panel-group
      .panel.panel-default
        .panel-heading
          %h4.panel-title
            = link_to 'How to connect with Slack', '#slack', 'data-toggle' => 'collapse', 'data-parent' => '#accordion'
        #slack.panel-collapse.collapse
          .panel-body.connect_instructions
            %ol
              %li
                Open your
                %b Slack team chat.
              %li
                Click on your
                %b Team menu
                and select
                %b Configure integrations.
              %li
                Select the
                %b Hubot
                integration and click on
                %b Add Hubot integration.
              %li
                Now you have a fresh, new Hubot integration. Take note of the
                %b Setup instructions. Use those to config your bot.
              %li
                Put your
                %b Deployator's url
                in the
                %b Hubot URL
                field.
              %li
                Finally, click on the
                %b Save
                button and you're done.
